review_blob: Pour from bottle, the liquid is black in color with little head. Smell caramel and coffee, though barely noticeable. It is thin and light bodied and rather flat. Taste lightly sweet bitter with no negligible aftertaste. Overall, I feel rather disappointed with this stout.
Overall this beer tastes like lemonade beer with a spice bitter aftertaste.

Pour from bottle, the liquid is medium bodied and light gold in color. Not very lively and flattens really fast. Smell very lightly alcohol and taste somewhat sweet, but leave a somewhat bitter aftertaste. Overall, its ok but really cant say that I love it.

Pour from bottle, the liquid is light gold in color, light body, and lightly carbonated. Smell a bit alcohol and taste bitter accompanied by similar aftertaste. While drinkable, definitely not my favorite German pilsener.

Pour from bottle, the liquid is light gold in color and lively but flattens fairly fast. Smell somewhat grass, barely noticeable. Taste bitter and leave a rather lasting bitter aftertaste. Overall, it is a refreshing and enjoyable mass market pilsener.

Pour from bottle, the liquid is light gold in color and lively, albeit flattens fairly fast. Smell citrus, taste lightly sweet. It is light bodied and has a lightly bitter aftertaste. Overall, this is a very refreshing beer.

Pour from can, the liquid is amber gold in color and lively. Smells floral. Tastes lightly sweet and somewhat bitter. The finish is also somewhat bitter and long for a lager. Its a good lager albeit pricey.

It belongs to the category of barely drinkable mass market lager. Pour from can, lively gold liquid with ample head that vanishes fast. Somewhat floral smell, somewhat sweet taste and somewhat alcohol aftertaste, all not very significant. The good thing about this beer is that its at least drinkable, but I would take his cousin Asahi Draft anytime any day.

Pour from can, gold color, lightly carbonated, moderate head that almost disappears as the liquid flows into the glass. Smells floral and caramel, tastes somewhat sweet. Aftertaste is sweet, lightly alcohol and lightly bitter. Overall, slightly better than those undrinkable lager.
Smell fruity and taste fruity. Little to no head, gold in color and liquid lively. Overall, a rather easy to drink cider.

Pour from bottle, the beer is very pale blond with ample head. Smell and taste alcohol albeit very very very light. Somehow I find this beer to be rather enjoyable, despite its shortcomings. Something that I can use to replace regular sodas sometimes.

Pour from bottle, this dark blonde beer is lively with lots of head. Smell floral and alcohol and taste lightly sweet and bitter. Medium body. The finish is somewhat bitter. While not bad in general, not particularly enjoyable for me somehow.
Pour from bottle, this cider is light gold in color, light bodied and lightly carbonated. Smell floral and taste fruity with very subtle aftertaste. Something quite enjoyable in hot weather.
Nice sake to be tried chilled. Taste rice, smell rice and aftertaste again rice. Generally, this a rather full bodied sake with ample rice sweetness (though labelled as dry) to me.
A nice premium cider with a fruity taste. Essentially like a dessert wine.

Blonde color, clear liquid, ample head, smell and taste a bit alcohol, a little bitter aftertaste. I wasnt expecting anything great, but somehow it turns out better than expected. Good choice among bad beers.
Probably one of the worst beer that Ive ever tried. It tastes almost like water with a couple drops of alcohol.
Drink directly from bottle, my first impression is: this is not something I enjoy drinking. Smells metal, like cheap alcohol and taste accordingly. Not a good alcohol free beer in my opinion.
Pour from can, lively light gold color liquid with adequate head that flattens fast. Smell metal, and taste accordingly with somewhat alcohol like aftertaste. Not a great pilsener in my opinion.
Pour from bottle, amble in color with adequate head, liquid is rather lively. Smell citrus and taste caramel with little aftertaste. Another typical German wheat beer.
Pour from bottle, dark color and rather flat, liquid isnt very fizzy. Smell caramel and taste so with a hint of bitterness. Overall, too light to be a dubbel, but too strong to be a thirst quencher.

Pour from a bottle, aroma is there, caramel, check. Appearance so so as it flattens super fast, though the liquid is lively. Taste there, check. Palate, slight bitterness, ok, check. Overall, too sweet for my taste.
Dark blond color with a sweet taste, though drinkable, this is definitely not my idea of a good wheat beer.
Bad strong beer with foul taste and strange sweetness. Something not worth your money even though its cheap.
An ok pilsner overall. Light blonde liquid, smells little bit metal and leave a bitter aftertaste.
Pour from bottle, dark blond liquid with little head that flattens fast. Smell caramel and taste grain. A very easy to drink wheat beer.
Pour from bottle, dark clear liquid with adequate head that flattens fast. Smells caramel and taste grain with light bitter aftertaste.
Stronger version of the regular Carlsberg lager. Uninspiring. Its green bottle counterpart is better.
Relatively good mass market lager. Nothing to shout about though. Neither surprised nor disappointed.
Dont really have much to say about this mass market lager. Drinkable but just the usual stuff.

Its very refreshing. It tastes like wine. It has alcohol. Its something I can down a six pack in a sunny afternoon. BUT ITS NOT BEER. My all fours rating doesnt reflect my opinion of this superb product, just a protest against its listing here.
From bottle, light blond color with almost no head, this very light beer smells a little bit grain and tastes a little bit sour. Though nothing special, at least its drinkable.
Pour from bottle, this beer is dark gold in color with almost no head. Carbonation is low. Smell alcohol and taste corn and bitter. It has slightly bitter aftertaste.
Pour from can, this beer is light gold in color. Adequate head but flattens fast. Smell a little bit citrus and taste a bit corn and bitter. Overall, drinkable and better than I expected.

Pour from can, the liquid is clear gold in color. Head flattens very fast and its only moderately fizzy. Body light and texture thin, it smells alcohol and tastes somewhat metal, bitter. It leaves a bitter aftertaste.
Pour from bottle, the liquid is brownish and lively. Head is ample but flattens fast. Smell a bit caramel and taste somewhat grass to me. Its too weak and watery to my liking.

Pour from bottle, this beer is light gold in color with head that flattens very fast. Taste bitter, body light. Its a rather lasting aftertaste. Overall, its drinkable but not something I really like.
Pour from can, this beer looks gold and clear with almost no head. Smell a bit alcohol and it has the accompanying dry bitterness. Drinkable but not really enjoyable.

Pour from can, this beer is gold in color with head that flattens fast. The liquid is lively though. Smell and taste corn, metal along with somewhat bitter aftertaste. Drinkable but not something enjoyable to me.
UPDATED: NOV 6, 2014

Pour from a bottle, it is amber in color with adequate head that flattens fast. The liquid is rather lively. Smell raisin, taste quite sweet with a brief hint of bitterness. Its a lasting aftertaste. Overall, something nice to drink, in the mean time, something nice to sip as well.

Pouring from a bottle into glass, the color is blond. The head is adequate but flattens immediately. Its nowhere near as lively as its lager brother. Tastes citrus with some bitterness. To sum it up, this beer is way too shandy-like for me.

Just another mass market lager. Little head and flatten almost immediately. The liquid is rather lively though. Personally, I think it tastes like a slightly stronger version of Carlsberg. Rather disappointed. French are wine people not beer. Can I say I would prefer a Bud or a Tsingtao to this?
I like the slight wheat sweetness of this beer. Liquid is golden and head is full. Hops a bit floral and texture a bit creamy. A very nice wheat beer indeed.
Nothing too special, but dont have anything to complain either, knowing that its your typical lager. Light, easy to drink and accompany by a certain level of sweetness.
UPDATED: SEP 9, 2015

Another typical mass market lager. Not worth the word "Premium" on its can, but nevertheless drinkable. Taste a bit alcohol, with slightly bitter aftertaste. Nothing to comment about, except Ive something even worse earlier.
Very light gold color with heat that flattens almost immediately, the liquid is lively and light. Taste a bit alcohol. Not something worth mentioning, but at least its refreshing.

Pour from a bottle, the liquid is dark brown with generous head. Smells like coffee, caramel and charcoal. Upon indulging, its creamy and leaves a lasting sweet bitter aftertaste. Hard to believe that something with such a high alcohol content is so easily drinkable.
Clear light golden color with ample head that flattens fast, this beer fizzles. Its smooth and lively. Finish is light bitter and it lasts. Something very enjoyable to me.
